727978f-a.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 20th Avenue
727978f-a.text:
Shore Boulevard, east side, between Twentieth (left) and Twenty-
first Aves. (right), showing an old house in Queens. In the foreground
is the East River.
July 10, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

727975f-b.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 20th Avenue
727975f-b.text:
(1) (2) and (3)
Shore Boulevard, east side, south of Twentieth Ave., showing in a
set of three views,from fore to background,the homes of A. and J.S.
Polhemus. Also seen is the New York Connecting Railroad Bridge. See
other views for more data.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(4)
TThe same, another angle, showing the home built by Jacob Rapelye
in 1760.
About 1927.
Arthur White.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

727976f-d.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 20th Avenue
727976f-d.text:
Shore Boulevard, east side, south of Twentieth Ave., showing in a
set of four views the homes ef A. and J.5. Polhemus from different angles.
All looking southward and showing the New York Connecting Railroad bridge
in the background.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE RECRODUCEDN.
